# Development Guidelines

## Build Commands (pnpm Workspaces)
- `pnpm dev` - Start all workspaces in dev mode (already started by developer)
- `pnpm build` - Build all workspaces. REQUIRED to check changes made.
- `pnpm type-check` - TypeScript validation across project. REQUIRED to run after changes are made.
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/server dev` - Server only (already started by developer)
- `pnpm --filter @ha-addon/client dev` - Client only (already started by developer)

## TypeScript
- Strict mode enabled in both client and server
- Shared types in `/types/index.ts`, imported as `@ha-addon/types`
- Use proper TypeScript interfaces for all data contracts

## Logging (Server)
```typescript
import { LOG } from '../utils/logger';
const logger = LOG('COMPONENT_NAME');
logger.info('message');
logger.error('message', error);
```
- Levels: ERROR, WARN, INFO, DEBUG (controlled by `LOG_LEVEL` env)
- Never log secrets or sensitive data

## Error Handling
- Graceful degradation over hard crashes
- Comprehensive error context in logs
- Clear user-facing error messages

## WebSocket
- Server: `WebSocketManager` handles connections, ping/pong, and broadcast
- Client: `useWebSocket` hook provides connection, subscribe, and request
- Extend message types in both `types/index.ts` and the WS event types

## API Routes
- All routes mounted under `/api` prefix
- Use Express Router pattern
- Access shared services via `req.app.locals`

## Changelog
- When documenting a release, follow `.cursor/rules/changelog.mdc` (user-facing bullets, newest first, version aligned with `package.json` / `config.yaml`).
